                <head>238. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On June 3 the United States and Argentina signed a General Agreement for a
                    Program of Technical Cooperation. The agreement was signed for the United States
                    by <persName corresp="#p_BWL1">Willard Beaulac</persName> and for Argentina by
                        <persName corresp="#p_LA1">Alfonso de Laferrere</persName> and entered into
                    force that same day. <pb facs="0508" n="474" xml:id="pg_474"/> For text, see 8
                    UST 811. Documentation on this subject is in Department of State, Central File
                    835.00–TA.</p>
            </div>
